translated: Dahlstedt, Gustaf Harald, chief engineer, Huskvarna, born April 29, 1885 in Kumla to clergyman J.D. and Hilma Larsson. Married to Hilma Karlgren in 1914 and had three children: Sigvor (born 1915), Widar (born 1920), and Torsten (born 1926). He completed his education at Örebro Technical Gymnasium (M) in 1905 and went on to study in Germany, Switzerland, Norway, and Finland. He worked in mechanical engineering and marine engineering in 1906, as a draftsman at Götaverken in 1907, and at various heating companies in Stockholm from 1908-1911. He served as department manager at Graham Brothers in Riga from 1912-1916, as factory manager of Husqvarna Weapons Factory in Petrograd in 1918, as chief engineer at Norrahammars Bruk in 1919, and as chief engineer at Stensholms Fabr. A-B in Huskvarna from 1921 onward. His hobbies were historical, genealogical, and racial research.

structured.description: Gustaf Harald Dahlstedt was a Swedish chief engineer known for his historical, genealogical, and racial research. He was born in Kumla to clergyman J.D. and Hilma Larsson on April 29, 1885. He completed his education at Örebro Technical Gymnasium in 1905 and went on to study in Germany, Switzerland, Norway, and Finland. He held various roles in mechanical and marine engineering, drafting, and management at companies including Götaverken, Graham Brothers, Husqvarna Weapons Factory, Norrahammars Bruk, and Stensholms Fabr. A-B. In 1914, he married Hilma Karlgren and they had three children: Sigvor, Widar, and Torsten.
